Damage caused by a fire in the Free State. PARLIAMENT - Parliament's Agriculture Committee has called on the national government to declare parts of the Free State and Northern Cape disaster areas following devastating fires in the provinces.
The fires, that began on Sunday, have destroyed farms in Hertzogville, Hoopstad, Bultfontein and Dealesville. READ: Free State fires contained for now Farmers have reported huge losses of property, livestock and game. At least one farmer has been admitted to hospital after being trapped in one of the blazes.